{"serial": "12002", "department_serial": 11, "code": "EL1203", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Colonial Formations of Modernity", "ch": "殖民現代性"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Yau Ching"], "ch": ["游靜"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 5, "session": ["6", "7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "A", "room": "108"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "英美語文學系", "en": "Department of English"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 49, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "本課程專門為鋪墊學生對英國文學、殖民主義、帝國主義、歐洲現代性輸出及後殖民文化構成的基本認知而設，並對思考文學敘事再現與文化政治的關係，將有助益。", "en": "This course aims to introduce critical approaches to the study of modernity in relation to colonial histories. Its goal is to equip students with critical knowledges and analytical skills: 1) to examine how (Anglo-European) modernity is represented as a universalized teleology of historical progress for all humanity; 2) to develop decolonial perspectives of reconsidering our historical relationship to the colonial formations of modernity in the mediated everyday life by our social practices, political ideas, economic life, and cultural expressions. This introductory course gives students an understanding of the historical conditions out of which the English department has developed in non-Anglophone societies and is designed to prepare students with essential knowledge and skills for critical Anglophone studies in the department."}, "outline": {"ch": "我們將以當代目光重新審視英語文學中對於帝國及殖民的思考，及殖民論述如何重塑全球族群、性/別與階級關係，亦會考量文學及電影呈現的文明價值、慾望，與道德倫理中的現代性。", "en": "Over the course of the semester, students will read selected literary, historical and cultural texts on colonialism from different historical periods and social perspectives. Students will be asked to study literary texts in relation to discursive texts. Students must complete assigned readings before class, be prepared to discuss the readings in class, raise and answer questions regarding each others’ presentations and projects."}, "textbook": {"ch": "理察·梅森：《蘇絲黃的世界》，1957。\n馬立博: 《現代世界六百年：15-21世紀的全球史與環境史新敘事》，向淑容譯，台北：春山出版，2022。\n李有成編: 《帝國主義與文學生產》，台北：中央研究院歐美研究所，1997。", "en": "Daniel Defoe, The Life and Adventures of Robinson Crusoe [1719]. https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/521\nRichard Mason, The World of Suzie Wong, 1957. \nhttps://archive.org/details/worldofsuziewong0000maso/page/n355/mode/2up\nAnthony Pagden, Peoples and Empires: A short History of European Migration, Exploration, and Conquest, from Greece to the Present. New York: The Modern Library, 2003.\nRobert Marks, The Origins of the Modern World: A Global and Ecological Narrative from the Fifteenth to the Twenty-first Century.  Lanham, Maryland: Rowman ＆ Littlefield, 2002.\nEdward Said, Culture and Imperialism. London: Vintage, 1994."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100%", "en": "100%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討\n實習/實驗", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar", "Practical Training Lab"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "第一週出席的學生及已讀過Robinson Crusoe 第1-4章及8-9章將被優先錄取。https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/521\n第一週小考 (必須通過) 15％ (Crusoe 第1-4章及8-9章);\n課上參與及討論 20％;\n小組研習 25％;\n課上報告 20％;\n辯論20％", "en": "Those who attend the first week, take the first quiz, and who have read the novel Robinson Crusoe Chs. 1-4 and 8-9 will be given priority to enroll. In-class discussion and presentation, training in independent research abilities and time management skills are essential components of this course. \nhttps://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/521\nFirst quiz 15％ (based on Crusoe Chs. 1-4 and 8-9);\nClass participation and discussion 20％; \nGroup research projects 25％;\nClass presentations 20％; \nFinal debate 20％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "Wed 2-5", "en": "Wed 2-5"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "以小組討論、研究提案、學生辯論及報告作為學習方法。同學運用最後兩週總結學習心得，及完成研究報告。", "en": "This seminar is designed as a student-tailored, project-based learning process. Students use the last two weeks to finish their final research projects and learn from group discussions."}, "domain": {"ch": "文學\n\n\n、\n\n\n文化研究\n\n\n、\n\n\n文學與文化研究", "en": "文學\n\n\n、\n\n\n文化研究\n\n\n、\n\n\n文學與文化研究"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "英文閱讀解析與寫作論述", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "英語溝通與文化跨越", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "審美欣賞與多元創意", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "自我評量/同儕互評"]}, {"competencies": "人文思維與社會關懷", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "組織能力與人際合作", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["出席/課堂表現", "自我評量/同儕互評"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "English critical reading and analytical writing", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "English oral communication and cultural crossing", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Research Report(printed on paper)", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "aesthetic appreciation and creative diversity", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Self Assessment/ Peer Assessment"]}, {"competencies": "humanities visions and social intervention", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "organizational ability and team work", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Attendance/Performance", "Self Assessment/ Peer Assessment"]}]}, "assignCriteria": {"ch": ["系所:限英美語文學系。年級:限一年級。", "系所:限輔系-英美語文學系、雙主修-英美語文學系、第二專長-英美文學與文化研究。"], "en": ["Department:Department of English only.Year:First Year only.", "Department:Minor-English、Double Major-Department of English、Minor Specialty-British and American Literature and Cultural Studies only."]}, "preselecStu": 49, "stuGender": {"male": 17, "Female": 32}, "stuGrade": {"doctor": {}, "master": {}, "bachelor": {"4": 2, "3": 1, "